definitions.definition: Someone (traditionally a woman) employed to look after the home , typically by managing domestic servants or superintending household management; also someone with equivalent duties in a hotel , institution etc.
examples: She was their third housekeeper , but after a month or so she also gave up.

definitions.definition: Someone who manages the running of a home , traditionally the female head of the household.
Someone who keeps to their house; someone who rarely ventures away from home; an unadventurous person, a homebody .
Someone who owns a house as a place of residence; a householder .

main_definition: Someone (traditionally a woman) employed to look after the home , typically by managing domestic servants or superintending household management; also someone with equivalent duties in a hotel , institution etc. [from 16th c.]
secondary_definitions: Someone who manages the running of a home , traditionally the female head of the household. [from 17th c.]
( colloquial , now rare ) Someone who keeps to their house; someone who rarely ventures away from home; an unadventurous person, a homebody . [from 18th c.]
( now rare ) Someone who owns a house as a place of residence; a householder . [from 15th c.]
